HEADWORD: airfoil
<hw>air"foil`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>a surface
such as the wing of an airplane designed to provide reactive force when
in motion relative to the surrounding air.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> aerofoil</syn>⟦br⟧
